<h3 id="mental-health-resources">Mental Health Resources</h3>

<p>If you experience significant stress or worry, changes in mood, or problems eating or sleeping this semester, whether because of CIS 110 or other courses or factors, please do not hesitate to reach out immediately, at any hour, to any of the course staff to discuss. Everyone can benefit from support during challenging times. Not only are we happy to listen and make accommodations, we can also refer you to additional support structures on campus, including, but not limited to:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="https://www.vpul.upenn.edu/caps">Counseling and Psychological Services (CAPS)</a>: 215-898-7021 (off hours and weekends 215-349-5490)</li>
  <li>Programs for Student Wellness through the <a href="https://www.vpul.upenn.edu/">VPUL</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.vpul.upenn.edu/shs/">Student Health Services</a></li>
  <li><a href="https://www.vpul.upenn.edu/rap-online/">Reach-a-Peer Helpline (RAP-line)</a> which is available nightly from 9pm-1am at 215-573-2727; you can text them anytime at 215-515-7332.</li>
</ul>

<p>If you or someone you know is in distress and poses an immediate danger to self or others please contact the Department of Public Safety at 215-898-7333, or 511.</p>
